/ In1956AlcuazsetupastudioinBarcelonawhichhemaintainedforfortyyears/ ./ HebecamepartofLaPu/ ñ/ alada/ ,/ aninformalgroupthatincludedtheCatalanartistsT/ à/ pies/ ,/ Tharrats/ ,/ Cuixart/ ,/ Aragones/ ,/ andAlumaamongothers/ ./ Theyweretheexponentsof/ '/ neofigurativism/ '/ andweretheforerunnersofmodernandcontemporaryartinSpain/ ./ LaPu/ ñ/ aladawasthenameofacafeinPaseodeGraciainBarcelona/ ,/ wheretheysocialized/ ,/ andtheterm/ (/ whichmeans/ :/ thestab/ )/ referstotheartofAndalusianknife/ -/ fighting/ ,/ whichhasmanyparallelswithflamencodancing/ ./ ThevisualartistsofLaPu/ ñ/ aladaidealisedthispurityofenergyandpassion/ ,/ andAlcuazhadbeenobservedtowieldhisbrushasifitwereafencingfoil/ ./ 
